messages.content: What is the purpose of the ComfyuiImageBlender custom node?
The ComfyuiImageBlender custom node is used to blend two images together using various blending modes.
How many blending modes are supported by the ComfyuiImageBlender custom node?
The ComfyuiImageBlender custom node supports 88 blending modes.
What are the three main blending modes categories supported by the ComfyuiImageBlender custom node?
The three main blending modes categories supported by the ComfyuiImageBlender custom node are Arithmetic, Binary, and Lighten.
Can the ComfyuiImageBlender custom node handle mask and strength parameters?
Yes, the ComfyuiImageBlender custom node supports mask and strength parameters.
What blending modes are included in the Darken group?
The Darken group includes the blending modes 'burn', 'darken', 'darker color', 'easy burn', 'fog darken', and 'gamma dark'.
What blending modes are included in the HSV group?
The HSV group includes the blending modes 'color hsv', 'hue hsv', 'saturation hsv', 'value', 'decrease saturation hsv', 'increase saturation hsv', 'decrease value', and 'increase value'.
Can the ComfyuiImageBlender custom node support more blending modes in the future?
Yes, the ComfyuiImageBlender custom node can support 45 more blending modes in the future.
